  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic Implant Stress Prediction Credibility Assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for finite-element stress prediction of a tibial tray component under physiological loading conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can predict peak von Mises stress and fatigue life for a Class II orthopedic knee implant at Model Risk Level 3. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are fully assessed with both required and achieved levels populated, and achievedLevel meets or exceeds requiredLevel for every factor. Sensitivity analysis was performed varying cortical bone modulus (±20%), implant-bone interface friction coefficient (0.1–0.6), and tibial plateau loading magnitude (700–2100 N). Decision: Accepted.",
